00:20:32,166 --> 00:20:33,799
and was later re-elected during Biden's term,

820
00:20:33,799 --> 00:20:35,366
so his term expires in 2026.

821
00:20:35,366 --> 00:20:36,666
Trump can

822
00:20:36,666 --> 00:20:37,799
announce the next chairman in advance

823
00:20:37,799 --> 00:20:39,166
as Nixon did to Martin

824
00:20:39,166 --> 00:20:41,466
and use this "shadow chairman" to sideline Powell,

825
00:20:41,466 --> 00:20:42,966
but he has not done it so far.

826
00:20:42,966 --> 00:20:43,733
But let me tell you,

827
00:20:43,733 --> 00:20:45,899
if Trump actually wants to influence the Fed,

828
00:20:45,899 --> 00:20:47,133
he doesn't necessarily have 

829
00:20:47,133 --> 00:20:47,933
to target Powell alone,

830
00:20:47,933 --> 00:20:50,299
because the Fed has a very important feature

831
00:20:50,299 --> 00:20:51,733
that is, he is not alone.

832
00:20:52,566 --> 00:20:54,899
In fact, all major decisions of the Fed

833
00:20:54,899 --> 00:20:55,533
are

834
00:20:55,533 --> 00:20:57,933
jointly decided by

835
00:20:57,933 --> 00:20:59,466
the Federal Open Committee (FOMC), which is composed of 12 people.

836
00:20:59,466 --> 00:21:01,566
The weight of each vote here is the same,

837
00:21:01,566 --> 00:21:02,166
so in theory,

838
00:21:02,166 --> 00:21:04,666
the chairman does not have more voting power

839
00:21:04,666 --> 00:21:06,166
and it does not mean that all of it is up to the chairman.

840
00:21:06,966 --> 00:21:08,100
So for Trump,

841
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:10,700
assuming that he can control the majority of these 12 people,

842
00:21:10,700 --> 00:21:12,800
he can control and influence the Fed's decision-making.

843
00:21:13,266 --> 00:21:14,066
From a mechanism perspective,

844
00:21:14,066 --> 00:21:15,233
7 of the 12 people

845
00:21:15,233 --> 00:21:16,766
are appointed by the government

846
00:21:16,766 --> 00:21:18,799
and 5 are from local reserve bank presidents.

847
00:21:18,799 --> 00:21:20,599
Those who are interested in

848
00:21:20,600 --> 00:21:21,133
how they are rotated and selected

849
00:21:21,133 --> 00:21:22,766
can go to watch the video we talked about the Federal Reserve.

850
00:21:22,766 --> 00:21:24,166
In short, he has so many people making decisions together

851
00:21:24,166 --> 00:21:25,966
in order to balance

852
00:21:25,966 --> 00:21:27,733
the relationship between the government, the bank, and the market.

853
00:21:27,733 --> 00:21:29,600
But even the 7 people chosen by the government

854
00:21:29,600 --> 00:21:30,866
cannot be replaced at will.

855
00:21:30,866 --> 00:21:32,933
Everyone has an extra-long term of 14 years,

856
00:21:32,933 --> 00:21:34,066
and one expires every two years

857
00:21:34,066 --> 00:21:34,933
For example,

858
00:21:34,933 --> 00:21:36,666
although Powell's term as chairman expires in 2026,

859
00:21:36,666 --> 00:21:38,999
his term as a director will not end until 2028.

860
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:40,566
So even if he retires next year,

861
00:21:40,566 --> 00:21:42,933
he will most likely still be a director

862
00:21:42,933 --> 00:21:43,766
in this team of 12 people,

863
00:21:43,766 --> 00:21:44,999
and he will still have voting rights.

864
00:21:45,500 --> 00:21:46,500
In fact, the way the government

865
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:48,299
has always tried to influence the Fed

866
00:21:48,299 --> 00:21:49,333
in addition to appointing the chairman,

867
00:21:49,333 --> 00:21:52,700
is to stuff more doves into the FOMC.

868
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:54,733
Doves are those who advocate monetary easing.

869
00:21:54,733 --> 00:21:56,899
Generally, when people analyse the monetary policy of the Fed,

870
00:21:56,899 --> 00:21:59,066
they will analyse these 12 people. Who is a hawk

871
00:21:59,066 --> 00:21:59,766
and who is a dove

872
00:21:59,766 --> 00:22:00,566
It is very obvious

873
00:22:00,566 --> 00:22:01,533
what each person's inclination is.

874
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:02,933
We can see that

875
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:04,566
most of the seven people chosen by the government tend to be dovish

876
00:22:04,566 --> 00:22:07,033
The hawks basically come from the reserve bank.

877
00:22:07,033 --> 00:22:09,533
The White House is continuously

878
00:22:09,533 --> 00:22:11,166
influencing the Fed's decision-making indirectly through personnel appointments

879
00:22:11,166 --> 00:22:12,299
But at this point in time,

880
00:22:12,299 --> 00:22:13,666
it is impossible for him to replace all seven people at once,

881
00:22:13,666 --> 00:22:16,333
so it is still difficult to achieve immediate results.

882
00:22:16,333 --> 00:22:17,733
Another possible way

883
00:22:17,733 --> 00:22:19,000
for Trump to interfere with the Fed

884
00:22:19,000 --> 00:22:20,133
is through executive orders.

885
00:22:20,133 --> 00:22:21,733
Although it is difficult to change legislation

886
00:22:21,733 --> 00:22:23,766
the president can use executive orders

887
00:22:23,766 --> 00:22:25,566
to temporarily restrict the Fed.

888
00:22:25,566 --> 00:22:26,366
For example, in February of this year,

889
00:22:26,366 --> 00:22:29,133
Trump issued an executive order No. 14215 requiring all independent agencies

890
00:22:29,133 --> 00:22:32,000
to submit major regulations to the White House for review

891
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,566
before issuing major regulations

892
00:22:33,566 --> 00:22:35,399
and you must communicate with the White House regularly

893
00:22:35,399 --> 00:22:37,166
You see, this is actually what we mentioned before.

894
00:22:37,166 --> 00:22:38,066
Trump and Bessent

895
00:22:38,066 --> 00:22:40,266
want to limit the Fed's regulatory power

896
00:22:40,266 --> 00:22:41,466
and want it to relax regulation.

897
00:22:41,466 --> 00:22:42,766
In fact, in addition to these two tricks, the most common way for

898
00:22:42,766 --> 00:22:45,133
Trump to influence the Fed

899
00:22:45,166 --> 00:22:46,599
is through public opinion

900
00:22:46,733 --> 00:22:48,000
saying that Europe has cut interest rates,

901
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:48,799
why haven't you cut them yet?

902
00:22:48,799 --> 00:22:50,399
If the US economy continues like this, it will be over.

903
00:22:50,399 --> 00:22:51,899
Powell, you are always too late,

904
00:22:51,899 --> 00:22:53,333
always wrong, always Too Late

905
00:22:53,333 --> 00:22:55,100
in short, he wants to use these to influence public opinion

906
00:22:55,100 --> 00:22:56,100
and put pressure on the Federal Reserve.

907
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:57,066
However, it seems that

908
00:22:57,066 --> 00:22:58,566
the effect of this move is not very obvious

909
00:22:58,566 --> 00:23:00,133
and it is even a bit counterproductive.

910
00:23:01,233 --> 00:23:03,466
In fact, although Trump is the president of the United States,

911
00:23:03,466 --> 00:23:05,533
it can be said that there are few people on the earth who have more power than him

912
00:23:05,533 --> 00:23:07,166
But one of the institutions that left him feeling most helpless

913
00:23:07,166 --> 00:23:10,233
and at a loss was the Federal Reserve.

914
00:23:11,133 --> 00:23:13,666
You can see that he can directly throw various heavy policies

915
00:23:13,666 --> 00:23:15,333
at other departments, organizations, and even countries

916
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:16,399
He was harsher than anyone

917
00:23:16,399 --> 00:23:17,333
in his criticism of the Federal Reserve

918
00:23:17,333 --> 00:23:19,933
yet when it came to actual, tangible action

919
00:23:19,966 --> 00:23:20,666
he made no move at all.

920
00:23:20,666 --> 00:23:22,533
He just couldn't help but threaten to fire Powell,

921
00:23:22,533 --> 00:23:23,699
but he gave in within a week.

922
00:23:23,700 --> 00:23:24,799
For example, the executive order

923
00:23:24,799 --> 00:23:26,299
everything must be reported to the White House. 

924
00:23:26,299 --> 00:23:28,199
Although the power of the Fed has been weakened

925
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,733
it only dares to focus on supervision

926
00:23:29,733 --> 00:23:30,700
because the executive order

927
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:32,366
specifically adds a clause

928
00:23:32,366 --> 00:23:34,299
that does not include the monetary policy of the Fed

929
00:23:34,299 --> 00:23:35,799
That is, the monetary policy of the Fed

930
00:23:35,799 --> 00:23:37,033
does not need to be reviewed by the White House.

931
00:23:37,033 --> 00:23:37,566
Why?

932
00:23:37,566 --> 00:23:38,866
There is no need for it to add this clause.

933
00:23:38,866 --> 00:23:40,666
This actually indirectly confirms a logic

934
00:23:40,666 --> 00:23:42,199
that the White House dare not.

935
00:23:42,266 --> 00:23:43,066
Although it wants to

936
00:23:43,066 --> 00:23:44,299
it dare not interfere too much

937
00:23:44,299 --> 00:23:45,566
in the policy of the Federal Reserve.

938
00:23:45,566 --> 00:23:46,299
Even if it wants to try

939
00:23:46,299 --> 00:23:47,766
it is extremely cautious

940
00:23:47,766 --> 00:23:48,533
because the Federal Reserve

941
00:23:48,533 --> 00:23:50,099
is not simply an independent institution.

942
00:23:50,100 --> 00:23:51,500
There are people backing it up.

943
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:53,366
What has a deterrent effect on the US government

944
00:23:53,366 --> 00:23:54,800
is the trust of the market.

945
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:57,599
You can see that from 1951 to the present,

946
00:23:57,600 --> 00:23:59,066
Martin, Walker, Greenspan,

947
00:23:59,066 --> 00:24:00,533
Bernanke, Yellen, and Powell

948
00:24:00,533 --> 00:24:01,166
have built up

949
00:24:01,166 --> 00:24:01,933
this sustainable market trust

950
00:24:01,933 --> 00:24:03,666
bit by bit

951
00:24:03,666 --> 00:24:04,733
because of this trust

952
00:24:04,733 --> 00:24:06,533
the US dollar become an international reserve currency

953
00:24:06,533 --> 00:24:08,599
allows global capital and global central banks

954
00:24:08,600 --> 00:24:09,700
to invest in the US dollar

955
00:24:09,700 --> 00:24:10,533
without too many concerns.

956
00:24:10,533 --> 00:24:11,666
I dare say that this trust

957
00:24:11,666 --> 00:24:14,366
far exceeds the market's trust in the US government.

958
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:15,766
You see, tariffs

959
00:24:15,766 --> 00:24:16,699
sound very important.

960
00:24:16,700 --> 00:24:17,700
They connect so many countries.

961
00:24:17,700 --> 00:24:18,700
We also analysed it in the last issue.

962
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:20,866
The actual GDP of imports is only 3 trillion US dollars.

963
00:24:20,866 --> 00:24:22,666
The scope is wide, but the degree of connection is not so close

964
00:24:22,666 --> 00:24:24,166
The financial market is different.

965
00:24:24,166 --> 00:24:24,666
You can say that

966
00:24:24,666 --> 00:24:27,099
it is deeply connected to the bone marrow of the United States

967
00:24:27,100 --> 00:24:28,466
Whether it is government bonds,

968
00:24:28,466 --> 00:24:29,700
bonds of all large companies, or

969
00:24:29,700 --> 00:24:30,933
stocks of all large companies,

970
00:24:30,933 --> 00:24:31,999
they are all based on

971
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:33,699
the global market's trust in the US financial market

972
00:24:33,700 --> 00:24:34,600
and the US dollar

973
00:24:34,600 --> 00:24:36,333
The main pillar behind this

974
00:24:36,333 --> 00:24:37,466
is the Federal Reserve.

975
00:24:38,399 --> 00:24:40,699
So it is one thing for Trump to force him to cut interest rates,

976
00:24:40,700 --> 00:24:42,799
but if they accidentally undermine the foundation of the dollar

977
00:24:42,799 --> 00:24:43,699
things could go really bad.

978
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:45,366
Bessent has repeatedly warned the White House that

979
00:24:45,366 --> 00:24:47,733
firing Powell may cause market turmoil

980
00:24:49,066 --> 00:24:51,066
However, Trump's recent series of actions

981
00:24:51,066 --> 00:24:52,700
have indeed shaken the market's trust

982
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:53,500
in the dollar.

983
00:24:53,500 --> 00:24:54,066
Other countries

984
00:24:54,066 --> 00:24:55,799
are more or less de-dollarizing

985
00:24:55,799 --> 00:24:56,533
to a certain extent.

986
00:24:57,533 --> 00:24:59,066
Although the market generally believes that

987
00:24:59,066 --> 00:25:00,200
Trump dare not touch the Federal Reserve

988
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,933
and he dare not weaken the independence of the Federal Reserve

989
00:25:01,933 --> 00:25:02,899
but they are still worried

990
00:25:02,899 --> 00:25:04,366
that if he is in a bad mood one day, he will

991
00:25:04,366 --> 00:25:05,299
come up with a policy.

992
00:25:05,299 --> 00:25:06,699
If this really happens,

993
00:25:06,700 --> 00:25:07,899
it will be a real black swan event

994
00:25:07,899 --> 00:25:09,766
for the market .

995
00:25:10,799 --> 00:25:11,333
Mr. President,

996
00:25:11,333 --> 00:25:12,200
I want you to know that

997
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:13,433
I have lowered the discount rate

998
00:25:13,433 --> 00:25:14,666
to help you become president.

999
00:25:15,466 --> 00:25:16,600


1000
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:18,366
It ushered in

1001
00:25:18,366 --> 00:25:19,399
the highlight moment

1002
00:25:19,399 --> 00:25:20,366
Paul Walker

1003
00:25:20,366 --> 00:25:21,666
it rhymes

1004
00:25:21,833 --> 00:25:23,399
It is called the Walker miracle .

1005
00:25:23,399 --> 00:25:24,299
I added it myself.

